# Use Project Design System for UI Work

When creating a new UI or redesigning any existing UI in this project, always follow `DESIGN.md` as the single source of truth.

## Required

- Read and apply the typography, color palette, spacing, component styling, and responsive rules from `DESIGN.md`.
- Keep visual choices aligned with the design system's do and don't guidelines.
- Match existing project UI decisions to avoid introducing a parallel style language.

## Not Allowed

- Do not introduce new visual styles that conflict with `DESIGN.md`.
- Do not invent ad-hoc color, typography, spacing, or component patterns when a system pattern already exists.

## Example

- For a new button or CTA, reuse the button styles and hierarchy defined in `DESIGN.md` instead of creating a new visual variant.
